# Experience Perfection and Momentum Protection Standard™ (132)

**Full document:** `docs/constitution/132_EXPERIENCE_PERFECTION_AND_MOMENTUM_PROTECTION_STANDARD.md`

**Binding product law** for momentum, polish, and intentional navigation. Complements **128** (simplicity / cognitive load) and **131** (Create intent) — does not replace them.

## Mission

Platform evaluated on protecting momentum. Preserve thinking, reduce interruption, maintain trust. Small inconsistencies interrupt cognitive flow — eliminate them.

## Constitutional principle

Never surprise the user. Never interrupt momentum. Never make recovery harder than continuation.

## Twelve rules (summary)

1. Protect momentum above everything — when two behaviors are valid, choose the less interruptive  
2. Intentional navigation — Escape closes / collapses / cancels / dismisses before changing location  
3. Protect in-progress thinking — unfinished work needs an intentional leave decision  
4. One navigation path — one obvious route to each major destination  
5. Interface truthfulness — progress, counts, labels, statuses, steps, Current Focus always agree  
6. Never create hidden anxiety — no “4 steps / 3 visible” doubt  
7. Progressive disclosure stays calm — optional panels must not become dashboards  
8. Momentum recovery — help continue (“Ready to continue?”) never “start over”  
9. Every interaction builds trust — remove uncertainty  
10. Interface polish matters — tiny issues erode trust at this quality level  
11. Measure momentum loss — hesitation, wrong nav, recoveries, abandoned work (not vanity clicks)  
12. Final 12/10 certification — six reviewer questions; any yes → keep refining  

## Ten-Second Rule™ (permanent release gate)

> Can a first-time user understand what to do within ten seconds without docs or teaching?

**No → do not ship.**

## Ultimate product principle

User almost forgets they're using the platform — “I just kept working.”

## Before shipping member-facing UX (all must pass)

- [ ] Least-interruptive behavior chosen when alternatives exist?  
- [ ] Escape dismisses layers before unexpected navigation?  
- [ ] Unfinished work requires intentional leave (soft recovery)?  
- [ ] One obvious path — no duplicate Create→Create mazes?  
- [ ] Counts / steps / labels / Current Focus truthful?  
- [ ] Ten-Second Rule passes?  
- [ ] 12/10 cert questions would all answer **no** (nothing interrupted / surprised / confused)?  

## Conflict rules

- **128** wins on complexity / architecture exposure / ADHD certification  
- **130** One Creation Rule — never silently create Work  
- **131** governs Create intent before confirmation  
- **132** governs momentum, navigation surprise, truthfulness, polish, Ten-Second Rule  

